The Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy is a program designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists even without prior knowledge in the field. The bootcamp covers a wide range of topics including Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, cloud security, penetration testing, and cyber threat intelligence analysis. Participants will also learn about managing risks using data loss prevention strategies and navigating compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST. The program lasts for 16 weeks and includes 3 live online classes per week. Class sizes are kept small with up to 16 people per class. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit the website: https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop